Description: Azure AI Health Insights provides an API that serves insight models, specific for Health & Life Sciences, that perform analysis and provide inferences to be used by a human.

Enums.Name: EncounterClass

AllowedValues.Name: InPatient
AllowedValues.Description: A patient encounter where a patient is admitted by a hospital or equivalent facility, assigned to a location where patients generally stay at least overnight and provided with room, board, and continuous nursing service.

AllowedValues.Name: Ambulatory
AllowedValues.Description: The term ambulatory usually implies that the patient has come to the location and is not assigned to a bed. Sometimes referred to as an outpatient encounter.

AllowedValues.Name: Observation
AllowedValues.Description: An encounter where the patient usually will start in different encounter, such as one in the emergency department but then transition to this type of encounter because they require a significant period of treatment and monitoring to determine whether or not their condition warrants an inpatient admission or discharge.

AllowedValues.Name: Emergency
AllowedValues.Description: A patient encounter that takes place at a dedicated healthcare service delivery location where the patient receives immediate evaluation and treatment, provided until the patient can be discharged or responsibility for the patient's care is transferred elsewhere (for example, the patient could be admitted as an inpatient or transferred to another facility.

AllowedValues.Name: Virtual
AllowedValues.Description: A patient encounter where the patient is not physically present for the encounter, such as in a telehealth encounter, phone call, or electronic communication.

AllowedValues.Name: HealthHome
AllowedValues.Description: Healthcare encounter that takes place in the residence of the patient or a designee

AllowedValues.Name: Corrected

AllowedValues.Name: Cancelled
AllowedValues.Description: The observation is unavailable because the measurement was not started or not completed (also sometimes called "aborted").

AllowedValues.Name: EnteredInError
AllowedValues.Description: The observation has been withdrawn following previous final release.

AllowedValues.Name: Unknown
AllowedValues.Description: The observation status is unknown.  Note that "unknown" is a value of last resort and every attempt should be made to provide a meaningful value other than "unknown".

Enums.Name: ObservationStatusType

AllowedValues.Name: Registered
AllowedValues.Description: The existence of the observation is registered, but there is no result yet available.

AllowedValues.Name: Preliminary
AllowedValues.Description: This is an initial or interim observation: data may be incomplete or unverified.

AllowedValues.Name: Final
AllowedValues.Description:
The observation is complete and there are no further actions needed. Additional information such as 'released', 'signed', etc would be represented using [Provenance](provenance.html) which provides not only the act but also the actors and dates and other related data.
These act states would be associated with an observation status of `preliminary` until they are all completed and then a status of `final` would be applied.

AllowedValues.Name: Amended
AllowedValues.Description: Subsequent to being Final, the observation has been modified subsequent.  This includes updates/new information and corrections.

AllowedValues.Name: Corrected
AllowedValues.Description: Subsequent to being Final, the observation has been modified to correct an error in the test result.

AllowedValues.Name: Cancelled
AllowedValues.Description: The observation is unavailable because the measurement was not started or not completed (also sometimes called "aborted").

AllowedValues.Name: EnteredInError
AllowedValues.Description: The observation has been withdrawn following previous final release.  This electronic record should never have existed, though it is possible that real-world decisions were based on it. (If real-world activity has occurred, the status should be "cancelled" rather than "entered-in-error".)

AllowedValues.Name: Unknown
AllowedValues.Description: The authoring/source system does not know which of the status values currently applies for this observation. Note: This concept is not to be used for "other" - one of the listed statuses is presumed to apply, but the authoring/source system does not know which.

Models.Name: AgeMismatchInference
Models.Description: A notification for age mismatch is displayed when the age mentioned in a document for a specific patient does not match the age specified in the patient information.

Models.Name: SexMismatchInference
Models.Description: A notification for a sex mismatch is displayed when the gender, personal pronouns, gender-related body parts, or gender-related procedures mentioned in a patient's clinical document are either inconsistent or do not match the gender specified in the patient information.

Properties.Name: sexIndication
Properties.Description: Sex indication : SNOMED CT code for gender finding.

Models.Name: LateralityDiscrepancyInference
Models.Description: A laterality mismatch occurs when there is a discrepancy between the clinical documentation and the ordered procedure (orderLateralityMismatch), a contradiction within the clinical document (textLateralityContradiction), or when no laterality is mentioned (textLateralityMissing).

Properties.Name: lateralityIndication
Properties.Description: Laterality indication : SNOMED CT code for laterality qualifier value.

Models.Name: CompleteOrderDiscrepancyInference
Models.Description: A complete order discrepancy is shown when one or more body parts and/or measurements that should be in the document (because there is a complete order) are not present.

Properties.Name: orderType
Properties.Description: Order type : CPT ultrasound complete code for abdomen, retroperitoneal, pelvis or breast.

Properties.Name: missingBodyParts
Properties.Description: List of missing body parts required by a complete order : SNOMED CT codes.

Properties.Name: missingBodyPartMeasurements
Properties.Description: List of missing body parts that require measurement by a complete order : SNOMED CT codes.

Models.Name: LimitedOrderDiscrepancyInference
Models.Description: A limited order discrepancy occurs when there is a limited order, but all body parts and measurements that are needed for a complete order are present in the document.

Properties.Name: orderType
Properties.Description: Order type : CPT ultrasound complete code for abdomen, retroperitoneal, pelvis or breast.

Properties.Name: presentBodyParts
Properties.Description: List of body parts found in the document : SNOMED CT codes.

Properties.Name: presentBodyPartMeasurements
Properties.Description: List of body parts that are measured according to the document : SNOMED CT codes.

Properties.Name: isGuideline
